itemDescription: British doctor, Anglican priest and philanthropist (1855–1939)

wikipedia_page.main: John Stedwell Stansfeld (16 December 1855 – 17 December 1939) was a doctor, Anglican priest and philanthropist in Oxford, England, who founded the Oxford Medical mission in Bermondsey, London, and the Stansfeld Oxford & Bermondsey Club Football Club in 1897.
